@node "Prologue" "Before reading..."

    English is my second language, learned using Amiga since 1987. Attention, I
known well only the english reading.  For those people who will comment too much
upon my errors I reply:

    @{b}@{i}"Est modus in rebus ultraque citraque non potest exsistere rectum"@{ub}@{ui}
                           (Oratius, I satira)

    In the first release of this package, "OLE" stood for Objects and Links
Exchanged.  During its developement I've found potentiality that I'd never have
thought.  So, because of my laziness, I don't need to change the name "OLE", but
the reader has to known that, from now on, its meaning is increased and still is
increasing, day by day.

                  @{b}@{i}"Good ideas develop with development."@{ub}@{ui}
                       Rocco "the dwarf" Coluccelli

    I've assumed that readers know something about the @{" ARexx language " link "Copyright" 0} and its
support libraries. Sorry, I can't insert any documentation about those without
permission of the respective owners.
@endnode

